name: Texas A&M football
summary: Texas A&M University, ranked 25th, upset the 9th-ranked Missouri Tigers in a college football game with a score of 41-10. The Aggies' victory serves as a rematch of last season's championship game. A&M's Devon Achane scored three touchdowns, contributing significantly to the triumph. The loss marks the first defeat for Missouri, which had previously enjoyed a 41-game winning streak. Analysts now question the legitimacy of Missouri's ranking, while praising A&M's potential for playoff success. The victory also sets the stage for an upcoming game between A&M and 24th-ranked Auburn University.
